  "description": "¶Entry conditions Use closure operators when you have:\nA partially ordered set (or complete lattice) of structures. A process that enlarges or completes a structure in a canonical way. A need to find the smallest structure that is \u0026ldquo;closed\u0026rdquo; — stable under the process. ¶Definitions A closure operator on a partially ordered set (P,≤)(P, \\leq) is a function c:P→Pc : P \\to P satisfying three properties [@davey_IntroductionLatticesOrder_2002; @erne_ClosureOperators_2009]:\n",
